Janicez M If you go back far enough in my family, our common ancestor and his family before him all had a special gift that we call Mate Kite, the literal translation is Dead See, and the term refers to those who can see the faces of those who have passed. At the time of mass colonisation in New Zealand, to convert to any faith of Christ was a safe move for many Maori families, and so my ancestors brother converted to Anglican. Since then, everyone on this side of the family does not have this gift. However, the gift is so strong within our genes that some of my close cousins do have it. Mostly everyone on the other side of our family has this gift. 
It's not something that can't be dealt with, as I see my cousins living their most normal lives as they could. However the new world likes to forget about our deeply spiritual rooted past. I believe many groups of native peoples across the globe who have been colonised in this way, have been tricked by our ancestors decisions to convert to faiths that do not serve us spiritually. They served us physically, which means nothing when that faith has no spirit in the first place.
